8139	[The pushforward-sections functor and its additivity]
8140	  \label{lem:pushforward_sections_functor}
8141	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.pushforwardSectionsFunctor,
8142	    AlgebraicGeometry.pushforwardSectionsFunctor_additive}
8143	  \uses{lem:higher_direct_image_presheaf}
8144	  Let \(j : U \to X\) be a morphism and \(W \subseteq X\) an open. The
8145	  \emph{pushforward-sections functor} \(\operatorname{pushforwardSectionsFunctor} j\,W :
8146	  U.\mathrm{Modules} \to \mathrm{Ab}\) sends an \(\mathcal{O}_U\)-module \(M\) to its sections
8147	  \(\Gamma(W, j_* M) = \Gamma(j^{-1}(W), M)\) --- the pushforward along \(j\), forgotten to
8148	  abelian groups, viewed as a presheaf and evaluated at \(W\). It is an additive functor, and
8149	  its \(q\)-th right derived functor applied to \(H\) computes the absolute cohomology
8150	  \(H^q(j^{-1}(W), H)\).
8151	\end{lemma}
8152	\begin{proof}
8153	  \uses{lem:higher_direct_image_presheaf}
8154	  The functor is the composite of pushforward \(\operatorname{pushforward} j\) (additive), the
8155	  forgetful functor to presheaves of abelian groups (additive), and evaluation at \(W\)
8156	  (additive). A composite of additive functors is additive; the additivity follows from the additivity of
8157	  each factor. The identification of its right derived functor with
8158	  absolute cohomology is the presheaf description of
8159	  Lemma~\ref{lem:higher_direct_image_presheaf}.
8160	\end{proof}
