8166	  \label{lem:toPresheafOfModules_additive}
8167	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.toPresheafOfModules_additive}
8168	  The functor \(\operatorname{toPresheafOfModules} X : X.\mathrm{Modules} \to
8169	  \mathrm{PresheafOfModules}(\mathcal{O}_X)\), sending a sheaf of \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules to its
8170	  underlying presheaf of modules, is additive: it preserves finite biproducts and the additive
8171	  structure on hom-groups.
8172	\end{lemma}
8173	\begin{proof}
8174	  The functor is the composite of the forgetful functor
8175	  \(\mathrm{SheafOfModules}(\mathcal{O}_X) \to \mathrm{PresheafOfModules}(\mathcal{O}_X)\) and the
8176	  restriction of scalars along the identity \(\operatorname{restrictScalars}(\mathrm{id}_{\mathcal{O}_X})\).
8177	  Both factors are additive, and a composite of additive functors is additive.
8178	\end{proof}
